rary team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2022-09-09T08:18:04Z", "updated_at": "2022-09-12T04:07:23Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "According to the gnu libc documentation sockaddr_in6::sin6_flowinfo is provided in network byte ordering (see https://www.gnu.org/software/libc/manual/html_node/Internet-Address-Formats.html), as is consistent with the other fields in sockaddr_in6 which appear directly in the ipv6 header.\r\n\r\nHowever, the rust's standard library SocketAddrV6 implementation does not do any conversion from network byte ordering on access: https://doc.rust-lang.org/src/std/net/addr.rs.html#481-483\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/101605/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/101605/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}